```plantuml
@startuml aws-solutions_iot-device-simulator
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor black
  Style roundrect
}
left to right direction

actor User

rectangle "Frontend GUI" as GUI {
}

rectangle "AWS IoT" as IoT #lightblue {
  rectangle "IoT Core" as IoTCore
}

rectangle "Microservices" as Microservices #lightyellow {
  rectangle "DeviceTypeManager" as DeviceTypeManager
  rectangle "SimulationManager" as SimulationManager
  rectangle "ResponseManager" as ResponseManager
}

rectangle "Simulator" as Simulator #lightgreen {
  rectangle "Device Generator" as DeviceGenerator
}

rectangle "AWS Step Functions" as StepFunctions #lightsteelblue

rectangle "AWS Lambda" as Lambda #mistyrose

rectangle "AWS CloudFormation" as CloudFormation #aliceblue

rectangle "AWS CDK" as CDK #lightgrey

' ========== Connections ==========
User --> GUI

' GUI interactions
GUI <--> Microservices : define device types\n manage simulations\n handle requests
Microservices --> DeviceTypeManager : CRUD operations for device types
Microservices --> SimulationManager : CRUD operations for simulations
Microservices --> ResponseManager : handle API requests

' Simulator interactions
SimulationManager --> Simulator : start/stop simulations
Simulator --> DeviceGenerator : generate and send data

' AWS IoT interactions
DeviceGenerator --> IoTCore : send simulated data

' Orchestration and Infrastructure
StepFunctions --> Simulator : orchestrate simulation processes
Lambda --> Microservices : execute microservice logic
CloudFormation --> AWS : deploy infrastructure
CDK --> CloudFormation : define infrastructure as code

@enduml
```